<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n29bfrc"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n29" href="#n29bfrc">N29 (VI.B.21)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n29all.htm#n29bfrc">back flyleaf recto(c)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> <span class="strike"><span class="striketext">ple</span></span> pelota / chistera </blockquote> <dd class="well"><mm class="note">Note: Spanish, &ldquo;little ball&rdquo;: a Basque ball game usually played against a front wall, either barehanded or with a leather or wooden glove-like protector (<i>cesta</i>, or with a <i>chistera</i> (a wickerwork implement three feet long in the narrow groove of which the ball is caught and flung back) strapped to the wrist. </mm> </dd></dl>
